the only organization in the\r\nUnited States that has as its core mission the commissioning of networked art by both emerging and established\r\nartists.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_81\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"298\"]<a href=\"http://demo.rtl.co.il/turbulence/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/i2.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-81\" src=\"http://demo.rtl.co.il/turbulence/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/i2-298x300.jpg\" alt=\"Networked Music Review (2007)\" width=\"298\" height=\"300\" /></a> Networked Music Review (2007)[/caption]\r\n\r\nNew American Radio, a weekly national radio art series, commissioned and distributed over 300 original works\r\nbetween 1987 and 1998, and was ranked with such high-profile programs as ABC Australia\'s \"The Listening Room,\"\r\nand Austria\'s \"Kuntsradio.\" Its works, which won numerous international competitions, were aired throughout\r\nNorth America, Europe and Australia. 300 full-length works have been archived at Wesleyan University, 140 at\r\nsomewhere.org.\r\n\r\nNew Radio and Performing Arts, Inc. thanks the Andy Warhol Foundation for the Visual Arts, the Jerome Foundation,\r\nthe LEF Foundation, the Massachusetts Cultural Council, mediaThe foundation inc., the Murray G. and Beatrice H.\r\nSherman Charitable Trust, the National Endowment for the Arts, the New York City Department of Cultural Affairs,\r\nthe New York State Music Fund, the New York State Council on the Arts, a State agency, The Greenwall Foundation,\r\nand Trust for Mutual Understanding for their support.','Our history','','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-v1','','','2015-05-03 13:30:09','2015-05-03 13:30:09','','22','http://demo.rtl.co.il/turbulence/22-revision-v1/','0','revision','','0'),('98','1','2015-05-03 13:59:40','2015-05-03 13:59:40','abe linkoln is a net artist and net curator. Recent works include \"My Boyfriend Came Back From the War (Abe Linkoln\'s 2004 Blog Mix)\" featured in the Last Real Net Art Museum, \"Netflix\" featured in Altx